{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, there are plenty of graph structures that appear naturally within Vision-Language tasks.",
    "This multitude of graph types allow for different structures to be taken for the image, from the semantic structure of an image to the hierarchical structure of the image with regards to the entire training set.",
    "Graphs appear naturally in the language component of the tasks as well, with sentence dependency trees being closely aligned to semantic graphs (when the semantic graph is made multi-partite as in the case of [80]).",
    "When clear graph representations of data exist, they should be utilised rather than ignored, instead of learning a graph structure using a more general purpose architecture.",
    "Utilising existing graph structures enables a graph network with the appropriate inductive biases to be deployed."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
